South Africa Auctions 800 Million Rand of Inflation-Linked Bonds

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-10-07T09:20:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/south-africa-auctions-800-million-rand-of-inflation-linked-bonds.html
South Africa  sold 800 million rand of
inflation-linked bonds maturing in 2022 and 2023 at a central
bank auction in  Pretoria  today.  The central bank sold 295 million rand of bonds due 2022 at
an average yield of 2.48 percent, and 505 million of notes due
2033 at a yield of 2.60 percent, according to its data on
Bloomberg. It didnâ€™t allocate any 2028 inflation-linked bonds.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
